### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8081
@staffEmail = staff@test.com
@staffPassword = staffpass

### ==========================================
### SETUP: LOGIN STAFF (To get token)
### ==========================================
# @name loginStaff
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "email": "{{staffEmail}}",
    "password": "{{staffPassword}}"
}

### ==========================================
### TEST 1: GENERATE BILL - SUCCESS
### ==========================================
# This should return a 201 Created and the new Bill data.
# Make sure to use a Room and Contract ID that actually exist in your database!

POST {{baseUrl}}/bills/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{loginStaff.response.body.data.access_token}} 
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "room_id": "ROOM-101",
    "contract_id": "CONT-101",
    "record_date": "2026-05-01",
    "due_date": "2026-05-05"
}

### ==========================================
### TEST 2: BR-02 VIOLATION - AVAILABLE ROOM
### ==========================================
# This tests our exact BR-02 logic. Put the ID of a room that 
# has the status "Available". The server should block it.

POST {{baseUrl}}/bills/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{loginStaff.response.body.data.access_token}} 
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "room_id": "ROOM-AVAILABLE-01",
    "contract_id": "CONT-999",
    "record_date": "2026-05-01",
    "due_date": "2026-05-05"
}

### ==========================================
### TEST 3: MISSING UTILITY USAGE DATA
### ==========================================
# This tests what happens if staff tries to generate a bill 
# before recording the water/electric meters for this contract.

POST {{baseUrl}}/bills/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{loginStaff.response.body.data.access_token}} 
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "room_id": "ROOM-102",
    "contract_id": "CONT-NO-METER-YET",
    "record_date": "2026-05-01",
    "due_date": "2026-05-05"
}

### ==========================================
### TEST 4: INVALID JSON / MISSING FIELDS
### ==========================================
# This tests the Controller's validation. We are purposely 
# forgetting to send the "contract_id" and "due_date".
# It should return a 400 Bad Request.

POST {{baseUrl}}/bills/generate
Authorization: Bearer {{loginStaff.response.body.data.access_token}} 
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "room_id": "ROOM-103",
    "record_date": "2026-05-01"
}